{"alignment_id": "shijing__guofeng-beifeng-006__001__zhwikisource-20260530__legge-sheking-1871-ocr", "work_id": "shijing", "section_id": "guofeng-beifeng-006", "alignment_type": "exact_or_near_exact", "confidence": 0.99, "order": 1, "section_unit": "poem", "segment_type": "stanza", "alignment_granularity": "stanza", "is_coarse_alignment": false, "coarse_alignment_reason": null, "source_segment_count": 1, "target_segment_count": 1, "chinese_ref": "詩經·國風·邶風·006.1", "chinese_text": "擊鼓其鏜，踴躍用兵，土國城漕，我獨南行。", "translation_ref": "擊鼓.1", "translation_text": "Hear the roll of our drums!\nSee how we leap about, using our weapons!\nThose do the fieldwork in the State, or fortify Tsou,\nWhile we alone march to the south."}
{"alignment_id": "shijing__guofeng-beifeng-006__002__zhwikisource-20260530__legge-sheking-1871-ocr", "work_id": "shijing", "section_id": "guofeng-beifeng-006", "alignment_type": "exact_or_near_exact", "confidence": 0.99, "order": 2, "section_unit": "poem", "segment_type": "stanza", "alignment_granularity": "stanza", "is_coarse_alignment": false, "coarse_alignment_reason": null, "source_segment_count": 1, "target_segment_count": 1, "chinese_ref": "詩經·國風·邶風·006.2", "chinese_text": "從孫子仲，平陳與宋，不我以歸，憂心有忡。", "translation_ref": "擊鼓.2", "translation_text": "We followed Sun Tsze-chung,\nPeace having been made with Ch'in and Sung;\n[But] he did not lead us back,\nAnd our sorrowful hearts are very sad."}
{"alignment_id": "shijing__guofeng-beifeng-006__003__zhwikisource-20260530__legge-sheking-1871-ocr", "work_id": "shijing", "section_id": "guofeng-beifeng-006", "alignment_type": "exact_or_near_exact", "confidence": 0.99, "order": 3, "section_unit": "poem", "segment_type": "stanza", "alignment_granularity": "stanza", "is_coarse_alignment": false, "coarse_alignment_reason": null, "source_segment_count": 1, "target_segment_count": 1, "chinese_ref": "詩經·國風·邶風·006.3", "chinese_text": "爰居爰處，爰喪其馬，于以求之，于林之下。", "translation_ref": "擊鼓.3", "translation_text": "Here we stay; here we stop;\nHere we lose our horses;\nAnd we seek for them,\nAmong the trees of the forest."}
{"alignment_id": "shijing__guofeng-beifeng-006__004__zhwikisource-20260530__legge-sheking-1871-ocr", "work_id": "shijing", "section_id": "guofeng-beifeng-006", "alignment_type": "exact_or_near_exact", "confidence": 0.99, "order": 4, "section_unit": "poem", "segment_type": "stanza", "alignment_granularity": "stanza", "is_coarse_alignment": false, "coarse_alignment_reason": null, "source_segment_count": 1, "target_segment_count": 1, "chinese_ref": "詩經·國風·邶風·006.4", "chinese_text": "死生契闊，與子成說，執子之手，與子偕老。", "translation_ref": "擊鼓.4", "translation_text": "For life or for death, however separated,\nTo our wives we pledged our word.\nWe held their hands; —\nWe were to grow old together with them."}
{"alignment_id": "shijing__guofeng-beifeng-006__005__zhwikisource-20260530__legge-sheking-1871-ocr", "work_id": "shijing", "section_id": "guofeng-beifeng-006", "alignment_type": "exact_or_near_exact", "confidence": 0.99, "order": 5, "section_unit": "poem", "segment_type": "stanza", "alignment_granularity": "stanza", "is_coarse_alignment": false, "coarse_alignment_reason": null, "source_segment_count": 1, "target_segment_count": 1, "chinese_ref": "詩經·國風·邶風·006.5", "chinese_text": "于嗟闊兮，不我活兮，于嗟洵兮，不我信兮。", "translation_ref": "擊鼓.5", "translation_text": "Alas for our separation!\nWe have no prospect of life.\nAlas for our stipulation!\nWe cannot make it good."}
